                        <p>The right-side <m>x</m>-intercept, <m>(183.515,0)</m>, represents the point when the missile hit its target; while the left-side <m>x</m>-intercept, <m>(-18.515,0)</m>, represents the point when the missile was launched. The difference between their <m>x</m>-values is the time of the missile's complete flight. So the missile traveled a total of <m>183.515-(-18.515)=202.3</m> seconds.</p></li>
